gkb:priority><sgkb:evidence_required>journey_type is hajj</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>Hijri date is 10 Dhu al-Hijjah</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>time window is night</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>active zone is Mina</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>user is stationary or moving within a limited radius in Mina</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:knowledge_intent>mina_overnight_guidance</sgkb:knowledge_intent><sgkb:notes>This node models the ritual act of spending the night in Mina, while FirstTashreeqNight models the corresponding religious time window.</sgkb:notes><sgkb:creator>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:creator><sgkb:title>Spending the night in Mina</sgkb:title><sgkb:data_identifier>SpendingNightInMina</sgkb:data_identifier><sgkb:publisher>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:publisher><sgkb:publication_date>2026-07-11</sgkb:publication_date><sgkb:summary>The Hajj ritual state of remaining in Mina overnight during the Hajj sequence, including the first Tashreeq night associated with the tenth day of Dhu al-Hijjah.</sgkb:summary><sgkb:keywords>Ritual</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>SpendingNightInMina</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Spending the night in Mina</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>المبيت بمنى</sgkb:keywords></owl:NamedIndividual><owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#Rami"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#Ritual" /><sgkb:label_en>Stoning of the Devil / Rami</sgkb:label_en><sgkb:label_ar>رمي الجمرات</sgkb:label_ar><sgkb:definition>The Hajj ritual of stoning the Jamarat, also called Rami, which takes place at three stone pillars in Mina.</sgkb:definition><sgkb:ritual_of rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HajjJourney" /><sgkb:follows rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#StandingInArafat" /><sgkb:follows rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#SpendingNightInMuzdalifah" /><sgkb:associated_place rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#JamaratPlace" /><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>jamarat_al_aqaba</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>jamarat_al_wusta</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>jamarat_al_sughra</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>mina</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:temporal_rule>{"calendar": "Hijri", "month": "Dhu al-Hijjah", "days": [10, 11, 12, 13]}</sgkb:temporal_rule><sgkb:spatial_rule>User is inside or near Jamarat-related geofences in Mina.</sgkb:spatial_rule><sgkb:movement_rule>Directional movement toward one of the Jamarat zones, slow movement in dense crowds, or stationary periods near the Jamarat area.</sgkb:movement_rule><sgkb:context_state>rami_performance_state</sgkb:context_state><sgkb:inferred_need>Ritual Guidance + Crowd Awareness</sgkb:inferred_need><sgkb:recommended_message_type>Guidance</sgkb:recommended_message_type><sgkb:priority>High</sgkb:priority><sgkb:evidence_required>journey_type is hajj</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>active zone is Jamarat-related or Mina</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>Hijri date is 10, 11, 12, or 13 Dhu al-Hijjah</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>movement is toward, within, or near the Jamarat area</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:knowledge_intent>rami_guidance</sgkb:knowledge_intent><sgkb:notes>The current spatial dataset contains Jamarat al-Aqaba and Jamarat al-Sughra. Jamarat al-Wusta is included in the ontology as a required concept and should be linked once its geofence is added.</sgkb:notes><sgkb:precedes rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HairShaving" /><sgkb:creator>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:creator><sgkb:title>Stoning of the Devil / Rami</sgkb:title><sgkb:data_identifier>Rami</sgkb:data_identifier><sgkb:publisher>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:publisher><sgkb:publication_date>2026-07-11</sgkb:publication_date><sgkb:summary>The Hajj ritual of stoning the Jamarat, also called Rami, which takes place at three stone pillars in Mina.</sgkb:summary><sgkb:keywords>Ritual</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Rami</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Stoning of the Devil / Rami</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>رمي الجمرات</sgkb:keywords></owl:NamedIndividual><owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HairShaving"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#Ritual" /><sgkb:label_en>Hair shaving or trimming</sgkb:label_en><sgkb:label_ar>حلق الشعر أو تقصيره</sgkb:label_ar><sgkb:alternative_labels>Halq</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Taqsir</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Shaving the head</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Trimming the hair</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>حلق الشعر</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>التقصير</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:definition>Hair shaving or trimming is the ritual act of shaving the head or shortening the hair to complete the required release from Ihram after the relevant Hajj or Umrah rites.</sgkb:definition><sgkb:definition_ar>حلق الشعر أو تقصيره نسك يتحلل به الحاج أو المعتمر بعد أداء المناسك المطلوبة؛ يكون في العمرة بعد السعي، وفي الحج غالبا بعد رمي جمرة العقبة يوم النحر.</sgkb:definition_ar><sgkb:ritual_of rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HajjJourney" /><sgkb:ritual_of rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#UmrahJourney" /><sgkb:follows rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#Sai" /><sgkb:follows rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#Rami" /><sgkb:context_state>hair_shaving_state</sgkb:context_state><sgkb:inferred_need>Completion + Exit Ihram Guidance</sgkb:inferred_need><sgkb:recommended_message_type>Guidance</sgkb:recommended_message_type><sgkb:priority>High</sgkb:priority><sgkb:creator>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:creator><sgkb:title>Hair shaving or trimming</sgkb:title><sgkb:data_identifier>HairShaving</sgkb:data_identifier><sgkb:publisher>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:publisher><sgkb:publication_date>2026-07-11</sgkb:publication_date><sgkb:summary>Hair shaving or trimming is the ritual act of shaving the head or shortening the hair to complete the required release from Ihram after the relevant Hajj or Umrah rites.</sgkb:summary><sgkb:keywords>Ritual</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>HairShaving</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Hair shaving or trimming</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>حلق الشعر أو تقصيره</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Halq</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Taqsir</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Shaving the head</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Trimming the hair</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>حلق الشعر</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>التقصير</sgkb:keywords></owl:NamedIndividual><owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#DayOfTarwiyah"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#ReligiousOccasion" /><sgkb:label_en>Day of Tarwiyah</sgkb:label_en><sgkb:label_ar>يوم التروية</sgkb:label_ar><sgkb:definition>The eighth day of Dhu al-Hijjah in the Hajj sequence, commonly associated with preparing for Hajj movement and presence in Mina.</sgkb:definition><sgkb:part_of rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HajjJourney" /><sgkb:precedes rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#DayOfArafat" /><sgkb:associated_place rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#MinaPlace" /><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>mina</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:temporal_rule>{"calendar": "Hijri", "month": "Dhu al-Hijjah", "day": 8}</sgkb:temporal_rule><sgkb:spatial_rule>User is in or moving toward Mina during the eighth day of Dhu al-Hijjah, or is in Makkah preparing to enter Ihram for Hajj.</sgkb:spatial_rule><sgkb:context_state>tarwiyah_day_state</sgkb:context_state><sgkb:inferred_need>Preparation + Guidance</sgkb:inferred_need><sgkb:recommended_message_type>Guidance</sgkb:recommended_message_type><sgkb:priority>Medium</sgkb:priority><sgkb:evidence_required>journey_type is hajj</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>Hijri date is 8 Dhu al-Hijjah</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>active zone is Mina, movement is toward Mina, or user is in Makkah preparing for Hajj Ihram</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:knowledge_intent>tarwiyah_preparation_guidance</sgkb:knowledge_intent><sgkb:notes>For a pilgrim who is in Makkah, has completed Umrah and exited Ihram, or is a Makkah resident intending Hajj, the eighth day of Dhu al-Hijjah is a preferred context for entering Ihram for Hajj. Delaying Ihram until the ninth day is permissible and should not be inferred as an invalid state.</sgkb:notes><sgkb:creator>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:creator><sgkb:title>Day of Tarwiyah</sgkb:title><sgkb:data_identifier>DayOfTarwiyah</sgkb:data_identifier><sgkb:publisher>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:publisher><sgkb:publication_date>2026-07-11</sgkb:publication_date><sgkb:summary>The eighth day of Dhu al-Hijjah in the Hajj sequence, commonly associated with preparing for Hajj movement and presence in Mina.</sgkb:summary><sgkb:keywords>ReligiousOccasion</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>DayOfTarwiyah</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Day of Tarwiyah</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>يوم التروية</sgkb:keywords></owl:NamedIndividual><owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#DayOfArafat"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#ReligiousOccasion" /><sgkb:label_en>Day of Arafat</sgkb:label_en><sgkb:label_ar>يوم عرفة</sgkb:label_ar><sgkb:alternative_labels>Day of Hajj</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Yawm Arafah</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>يوم الحج</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:definition>The ninth day of Dhu al-Hijjah and a central occasion in the Hajj journey associated with Arafat.</sgkb:definition><sgkb:part_of rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HajjJourney" /><sgkb:follows rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#DayOfTarwiyah" /><sgkb:precedes rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#MuzdalifahNight" /><sgkb:associated_place rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#ArafatPlace" /><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>arafat</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>jabal_al_rahmah</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>namirah_mosque</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>jabal_namirah</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>mashair_train_arafat_3_station</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:temporal_rule>{"calendar": "Hijri", "month": "Dhu al-Hijjah", "day": 9}</sgkb:temporal_rule><sgkb:spatial_rule>User is inside or near Arafat-related geofences during the Hajj journey.</sgkb:spatial_rule><sgkb:context_state>arafat_occasion_state</sgkb:context_state><sgkb:inferred_need>Spiritual Reflection + Reassurance</sgkb:inferred_need><sgkb:recommended_message_type>Faith</sgkb:recommended_message_type><sgkb:priority>High</sgkb:priority><sgkb:evidence_required>journey_type is hajj</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>Hijri date is 9 Dhu al-Hijjah or user is at Arafat</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>active zone is Arafat-related</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:knowledge_intent>arafat_reflection</sgkb:knowledge_intent><sgkb:notes>Day of Arafat is the ninth day of Dhu al-Hijjah and is often described as the Day of Hajj because standing in Arafat is central to Hajj. It should not be conflated with Day of the Greater Hajj, which is commonly associated with the tenth day of Dhu al-Hijjah / Day of Nahr.</sgkb:notes><sgkb:creator>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:creator><sgkb:title>Day of Arafat</sgkb:title><sgkb:data_identifier>DayOfArafat</sgkb:data_identifier><sgkb:publisher>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:publisher><sgkb:publication_date>2026-07-11</sgkb:publication_date><sgkb:summary>The ninth day of Dhu al-Hijjah and a central occasion in the Hajj journey associated with Arafat.</sgkb:summary><sgkb:keywords>ReligiousOccasion</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>DayOfArafat</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Day of Arafat</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>يوم عرفة</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Day of Hajj</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Yawm Arafah</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>يوم الحج</sgkb:keywords></owl:NamedIndividual><owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#MuzdalifahNight"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#ReligiousOccasion" /><sgkb:label_en>Night at Muzdalifah</sgkb:label_en><sgkb:label_ar>ليلة المبيت بمزدلفة</sgkb:label_ar><sgkb:alternative_labels>Muzdalifah overnight</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>المبيت بمزدلفة</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:definition>The night spent in Muzdalifah beginning after sunset on the Day of Arafat and before proceeding to Mina on the tenth day of Dhu al-Hijjah.</sgkb:definition><sgkb:definition_ar>تبدأ ليلة المبيت بمزدلفة من بعد غروب شمس يوم عرفة، وتمتد إلى ما قبل التوجه إلى منى في اليوم العاشر من ذي الحجة.</sgkb:definition_ar><sgkb:part_of rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#HajjJourney" /><sgkb:follows rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#DayOfArafat" /><sgkb:precedes rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#EidAlAdha" /><sgkb:associated_place rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#MuzdalifahPlace" /><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>muzdalifah</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:associated_zone_ids>mashair_train_muzdalifah_station</sgkb:associated_zone_ids><sgkb:temporal_rule>{"calendar": "Hijri", "month": "Dhu al-Hijjah", "day": 9, "starts_after": "sunset_on_day_of_arafat", "time_window": "after_sunset_to_fajr", "next_day": 10}</sgkb:temporal_rule><sgkb:spatial_rule>User is inside or near Muzdalifah-related geofences after leaving Arafat.</sgkb:spatial_rule><sgkb:context_state>muzdalifah_night_state</sgkb:context_state><sgkb:inferred_need>Rest + Ritual Reassurance</sgkb:inferred_need><sgkb:recommended_message_type>Hospitality</sgkb:recommended_message_type><sgkb:priority>High</sgkb:priority><sgkb:evidence_required>journey_type is hajj</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>time is after sunset on Day of Arafat or night before 10 Dhu al-Hijjah</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:evidence_required>active zone is Muzdalifah-related</sgkb:evidence_required><sgkb:knowledge_intent>muzdalifah_night_guidance</sgkb:knowledge_intent><sgkb:notes>This node models the time occasion, while SpendingNightInMuzdalifah models the ritual state performed in Muzdalifah during this night.</sgkb:notes><sgkb:creator>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:creator><sgkb:title>Night at Muzdalifah</sgkb:title><sgkb:data_identifier>MuzdalifahNight</sgkb:data_identifier><sgkb:publisher>Ghader Kurdi</sgkb:publisher><sgkb:publication_date>2026-07-11</sgkb:publication_date><sgkb:summary>The night spent in Muzdalifah beginning after sunset on the Day of Arafat and before proceeding to Mina on the tenth day of Dhu al-Hijjah.</sgkb:summary><sgkb:keywords>ReligiousOccasion</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>MuzdalifahNight</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Night at Muzdalifah</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>ليلة المبيت بمزدلفة</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>Muzdalifah overnight</sgkb:keywords><sgkb:keywords>المبيت بمزدلفة</sgkb:keywords></owl:NamedIndividual><owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#EidAlAdha"><rdf:type rdf:resource="https://github.com/ghadairesearch/SacredGeoKB#ReligiousOccasion" /><sgkb:label_en>Eid al-Adha</sgkb:label_en><sgkb:label_ar>عيد الأضحى</sgkb:label_ar><sgkb:alternative_labels>Day of Nahr</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Day of Sacrifice</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Day of the Greater Hajj</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>Yawm al-Hajj al-Akbar</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternative_labels>يوم النحر</sgkb:alternative_labels><sgkb:alternativ